# Clinical Safety

- RASQ supports therapist review and does not provide diagnosis.
- Never invent clinical findings.
- Avoid definitive wording such as "the patient has".
- Prefer cautious wording such as "may indicate" and "for therapist review".
- AI-generated clinical content must remain editable and reviewable.
- Measured values must remain separate from AI interpretation.
- Clinical Safety applies across all product domains.
- Preserve Arabic and English behavior.
- Patient safety and accessibility take priority over visual effects.
